These configuration files demonstrate system hardening steps applied on an Ubuntu 22.04 server to improve security and reduce exposure to some brute force attacks.

### Key Tasks
- Enforced key-based SSH authentication and disabled root login.
- Configured UFW firewall to allow only essential services.
- Installed and configured Fail2ban to mitigate brute-force attempts.
- Applied least-privilege principles to user accounts and permissions.

### Tools Used
- UFW
- Fail2ban
- OpenSSH
- Bash scripting